g.title: j3192408709
g.text: Or have you forgotten them all

g.title: j1103584509
g.text: You have a hell of a way of starting a conversation, you know that?

g.title: j23407284
g.text: Not touching THIS with a ten foot pole... [End.]

g.title: j815267547
g.text: Haven't forgotten them, we didn't have any. I don't count the Orokin.

g.title: j301889074
g.text: The gods, babas - Sol and Lua

g.title: j1248595005
g.text: I... hate to break it to you, but Sol and Lua aren't gods. One's a star and the other is a rock that's seen some shit

g.title: j3346131289
g.text: They aren't worshipped as gods anymore, I'm sorry. But Lua is still considered kind of sacred.

g.title: j2118792809
g.text: I can only speak for myself, and I was raised to worship the Orokin. And then I learned better.

g.title: j1856325474
g.text: They were assholes who thought they were above everyone else. Enough said.

g.title: j1066938659
g.text: They were a group of people who ruled over the Origin system. Who thought of themselves as gods.

g.title: j1191945133
g.text: Lua... well... It kind of got shoved in the void for a while.

g.title: j1897945831
g.text: It's complicated. A really long story. The short of it is, it's still very important, but not worshiped.

g.title: j202436182
g.text: Not the first time men dressed themselves as kings

g.title: j808266312
g.text: If it is half like what it sounds

g.title: j2703309676
g.text: Talk to me more of them another time

g.title: j412438138
g.text: The void is kind of like a non-dimension? It's sometimes black and white. It's weird. Kind of tingly.

g.title: j338598846
g.text: Whoa, back up. *I* didn't put her anywhere! I had nothing to do with it!

g.title: j616549528
g.text: I believe in myself and the people around me.

g.title: j2603550938
g.text: But I was in Duviri, dying repeatedly, when the Lotus decided to put Lua in the Void.

g.title: j1466424019
g.text: I was abandoned on a space ship and then stuck in my own personal hell while all that nonsense was going on.

g.title: j2370176047
g.text: Dying on endless repeat does that to you.

g.title: j2655797219
g.text: Dying on endless repeat does that to you.

g.title: j1304797100
g.text: Dying on endless repeat does that to you.

g.title: j2306192340
g.text: Dying on endless repeat does that to you.

g.title: j34978850
g.text: This kingdom of death of yours

g.title: j3944692918
g.text: Certainty in nothing is its own belief
And anyone who tells you otherwise is a fool

g.title: j1981085183
g.text: That's a motivational poster not a belief
But whatever brings you peace at night

g.title: j3095077587
g.text: Duviri was an alternate dimension I kind of... created? Sort of? By existing?

g.title: j1099665736
g.text: No, that's one thing they didn't do to me, thankfully.

g.title: j3461315482
g.text: Recognizing one is small in the face of everything is important

g.title: j1219767311
g.text: This kingdom of death of yours

g.title: j278143759
g.text: It was made out of the void plucked from my mind and made real. Manifestations of a frightened child.

g.title: j2474476882
g.text: Suppose it does that to you

g.title: j676624092
g.text: But it all went wrong when I grew up and wanted to leave. And they began killing me, again and again.

g.title: j117367644
g.text: They. Me. It's all the same. It's a long story.

g.title: j224858586
g.text: And La Flaca knows your face

g.title: j1336269049
g.text: The name means nothing to me
I want to know his soul
Who was this *they* that hurt you

g.title: j516813748
g.text: In a way, I think I understand

g.title: j3410322745
g.text: He wasn't real. He was a fictional character the void plucked from my head and turned into reality by my sheer presence.

g.title: j386498409
g.text: Would you want to tell me all about *your* darkest moments right now?

g.title: j42001120
g.text: Maybe we have more in common than I gave you credit for, babas
